# See https://help.github.com/articles/ignoring-files/ for more about ignoring files.
#
# GitHub: do not track secrets, local build outputs, or machine-specific junk.
# Vercel: production builds from a clean install (dependencies + env in dashboard;
# these paths are never "deployed" as artifacts from your machine).

# ——— Dependencies
node_modules/
.pnp
.pnp.js
.pnp.data.json
.pnpm-debug.log*
.yarn/*
!.yarn/patches
!.yarn/plugins
!.yarn/releases
!.yarn/versions
.pnp.*

# ——— Build / TypeScript (rebuilt on CI & Vercel; never commit)
.next/
out/
build/
dist/
.turbo/
*.tsbuildinfo

# ——— Testing & coverage
coverage/
.nyc_output/
playwright-report/
test-results/
.jest/
*.lcov

# ——— Environment & secrets (never commit; set in Vercel "Environment Variables" instead)
# Keep *example* files in git for new contributors:
.env*
!.env.local.example
!**/.env.example
# Extra patterns for local overrides (some tools don’t use .env* prefix)
*.pem
.envrc

# ——— Vercel (local linked project; not needed in the repo)
.vercel
**/.vercel

# ——— Cursor: ignore local data; version shared project rules
.cursor/**
!.cursor/rules/
!.cursor/rules/**

# ——— Editor & OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
Desktop.ini
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# ——— Debug & logs
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
*.log
logs/
debug_*.ndjson
*.stackdump

# ——— Caches
.eslintcache
.cache/
.parcel-cache/
*.pid
*.seed
*.pid.lock
